## Description
The **Pweb store&nbsp;**resource allows to&nbsp;configure a dedicated DA3 environment that can be used in batch and on-demand workflows when publishing Pwebs.

## Additional creation parameters
None.

## Resource editor
None.

## Deploy parameters
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Section

Field

Description

**Configuration**

**Tenant**

Select the tenant&nbsp;on which you want to deploy the resource from the drop-down menu.

**Store**

**Default store**

*(optional)* Select this option to&nbsp;connect the new Pweb store resource to the existing DA3 environment.

> Important

Only one default environment can exist for each account.

**Documents**

**Retention**

*(optional)* Select this option to enable document retention for this Pweb store.&nbsp;

If you enable the&nbsp;**Retention** option, in the **Retention period (days)** field&nbsp;enter the number of&nbsp;days after which the documents in the class will be deleted.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

If not set, the documents in the class will never be deleted (default setting).

> Important

Updating the retention of an existing deploy will affect all previously uploaded documents in the store.

**Encryption**

*(optional)* Select this option to activate encryption for the Pweb store. By doing so, all documents uploaded to this archive on the selected tenant will be encrypted.

If you enable the **Encryption** option, click on the&nbsp;**Key**&nbsp;field that appears to select the required&nbsp;**Store key** resource:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Important

Each Pweb store may be associated with only one Store Key client account.

Once the resource has been deployed on a tenant, it is no longer possible to disable the encryption option. It is only possible to deploy the resource again on the same tenant selecting a different Store Key resource; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

Click **Publish** to publish the release on the tenant.

Click **Deploy** to publish and enable the release on the tenant.
